LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 381
BY REVENUE AND TAXATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO TAXATION; AMENDING SECTION 63-3042A, IDAHO CODE, TO REVISE PRO-
3 VISIONS REGARDING EVIDENCE OF EXPENDITURES; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY
4 AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 SECTION 1. That Section 63-3042A, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
7 amended to read as follows:
8 63-3042A. EVIDENCE OF EXPENDITURES. For the purpose of documenting
9 an expenditure as a deduction or credit under this chapter, absent clear
10 and convincing evidence of fraud, a taxpayer's statement or invoice from
11 a credit card company or other financial institution reflecting the ex-
12 penditure shall conclusively establish that the expenditure was made by
13 the taxpayer, and the taxpayer's sworn statement that the expenditure was
14 made for an identified deductible purpose shall conclusively establish a
15 taxpayer's right to a deduction or credit. In any audit, assertion of defi-
16 ciency or other proceeding in which substantiation of a deductible expense
17 paid by credit card, debit card, or other electronic means is in question,
18 the state tax commission shall notify a taxpayer in writing of the provi-
19 sions of this section and retain proof that such notice has been provided as
20 required by this section.
21 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
22 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
23 July 1, 2025.

